1 A BILL for an Act to provide an appropriation to the department of commerce for tribal tourism
2 grants.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. APPROPRIATION - DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE - TRIBAL TOURISM
5 GRANTS. There is appropriated out of any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury, not
6 otherwise appropriated, the sum of $500,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, to
7 the department of commerce for the purpose of providing tribal tourism grants, for the biennium
8 beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. A tribal government in the state may apply to
9 the department of commerce for a grant of up to $100,000 to promote and enhance tribal nation
10 tourism opportunities.
